      "notes": [
        "Possessive Adjectives",
        "Rule: Possessives agree with the NOUN they describe, NOT the owner!",
        "1. Singular:",
        "   - My: mon (m), ma (f), mes (pl)",
        "   - Your (sing): ton (m), ta (f), tes (pl)",
        "   - His/Her: son (m), sa (f), ses (pl)",
        "2. Examples:",
        "   - mon père (my father - m)",
        "   - ma mère (my mother - f)",
        "   - son frère (his/her brother - m)",
        "   - sa sœur (his/her sister - f)",
        "3. Nigerian Context:",
        "   - Unlike English ('my' never changes), French changes based on the object's gender."
      ],
